Wow! These potatoes were fabulous and the dipping sauce 2 DIE 4! Couple of things... The instructions call for 3/4 tsp salt in the potatoes but its not listed in the ingredients. Also, i like my potatoes toasty brown so I ended up baking them for about 80 minutes and they were crispy perfect.

Rating: 4
This is easy enough to make on a weeknight and tasty enough for entertaining. I made these to accompany a steak for my husband and salmon for me...yum! I used the juice from one lime and all of the zest from the same lime and it worked perfectly (to avoid wasting the lime). Although, I thought this was perfect as is, I think I will double the cumin and oregano next time. I think they were both a little overpowered by the salt. I didn't bother with turning the potatoes and they turned out fine. Enjoy!

Rating: 4
This was excellent indeed and very versatile. Had fish already thawed so used it in place of chicken and made less coating (same proportions), coated only the tops, baked in 10 min...SUPERB! And the cilantro-lime mayo (made with light sour cream and mayo) was a great accompaniment! This was an excellent meal with a spinach salad and one my husband requests that we repeat. Nice fresh flavor. I also used limed tortilla chips which went nicely. Potatoes were great, too, they baked in only 30 min.

